@startuml OTP_Login
title OTP Login

actor User
participant UI
participant LoginEndpoint
participant MediatR
participant LoginHandler
participant Repository
participant Service
database Database

== Flow 1: OTP Login (Auto-register) ==

User -> UI: 1. Enter identifier + OTP
activate UI

UI -> LoginEndpoint: 2. POST /api/auth/login
activate LoginEndpoint

LoginEndpoint -> MediatR: 3. Send(request)
activate MediatR

MediatR -> LoginHandler: 4. Handle
activate LoginHandler

LoginHandler -> Repository: 5. GetValidOTP
activate Repository
Repository -> Database: 6. SELECT otp_codes
activate Database
Database --> Repository: 7. OtpCode
deactivate Database
Repository --> LoginHandler: 8. OtpCode
deactivate Repository

LoginHandler -> LoginHandler: 9. Verify Otp

alt OTP code mismatch
  LoginHandler -> Repository: 10. IncreaseAttemptCount
  activate Repository
  Repository -> Database: 11. UPDATE attempt_count
  activate Database
  Database --> Repository: Updated
  deactivate Database
  Repository --> LoginHandler: 12. Success
  deactivate Repository

  LoginHandler --> MediatR: 13. Response
  deactivate LoginHandler
  MediatR --> LoginEndpoint: 14. Response
  deactivate MediatR
  LoginEndpoint --> UI: 15. 401 Unauthorized
  deactivate LoginEndpoint
  UI --> User: 16. "Incorrect OTP"
  deactivate UI

else OTP code matches
  LoginHandler -> Repository: 10. GetUser
  activate Repository
  Repository -> Database: 11. SELECT users
  activate Database
  Database --> Repository: 12. User or null
  deactivate Database
  Repository --> LoginHandler: 13. User or null
  deactivate Repository

  alt User Not exists
    LoginHandler -> Repository: 14. CreateUser
    activate Repository
    Repository -> Database: 15. INSERT INTO users
    activate Database
    Database --> Repository: Inserted
    deactivate Database
    Repository --> LoginHandler: 16. Created
    deactivate Repository
  end

  LoginHandler -> Service: 17. GenerateToken
  activate Service
  Service --> LoginHandler: 18. accessToken, refreshToken
  deactivate Service

  LoginHandler -> Repository: 19. CreateRefreshToken
  activate Repository
  Repository -> Database: 20. INSERT INTO refresh_tokens
  activate Database
  Database --> Repository: Inserted
  deactivate Database
  Repository --> LoginHandler: 21. Success
  deactivate Repository

  LoginHandler --> MediatR: 22. Response
  deactivate LoginHandler
  MediatR --> LoginEndpoint: 23. Response
  deactivate MediatR
  LoginEndpoint --> UI: 24. 200 OK
  deactivate LoginEndpoint
  UI --> User: 25. Login success
  deactivate UI
end

deactivate handler
deactivate mediator
deactivate endpoint
deactivate ui

|||

== Flow 2: Password Login (Existing users only) ==

User -> UI: 1. Enter identifier + Password
activate UI

UI -> LoginEndpoint: 2. POST /api/auth/login
activate LoginEndpoint

LoginEndpoint -> MediatR: 3. Send(request)
activate MediatR

MediatR -> LoginHandler: 4. Handle
activate LoginHandler

LoginHandler -> Repository: 5. GetUser
activate Repository
Repository -> Database: 6. SELECT users
activate Database
Database --> Repository: 7. User or null
deactivate Database
Repository --> LoginHandler: 8. User
deactivate Repository

LoginHandler -> Service: 9. VerifyPassword
activate Service
Service --> LoginHandler: 10. true/false
deactivate Service

alt Password mismatch
  LoginHandler --> MediatR: 11. Response
  deactivate LoginHandler
  MediatR --> LoginEndpoint: 12. Response
  deactivate MediatR
  LoginEndpoint --> UI: 13. 401 Unauthorized
  deactivate LoginEndpoint
  UI --> User: 14. "Invalid credentials"
  deactivate UI

else Password matches
  LoginHandler -> Service: 11. GenerateToken
  activate Service
  Service --> LoginHandler: 12. accessToken, refreshToken
  deactivate Service

  LoginHandler -> Repository: 13. CreateRefreshToken
  activate Repository
  Repository -> Database: 14. INSERT INTO refresh_tokens
  activate Database
  Database --> Repository: Inserted
  deactivate Database
  Repository --> LoginHandler: 15. Success
  deactivate Repository

  LoginHandler --> MediatR: 16. Response
  deactivate LoginHandler
  MediatR --> LoginEndpoint: 17. Response
  deactivate MediatR
  LoginEndpoint --> UI: 18. 200 OK
  deactivate LoginEndpoint
  UI --> User: 19. Login success
  deactivate UI
end

@enduml
